  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.74,
      "text": "월간 굿모닝팝 3개월 구독권 보내드릴게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 3.76,
      "end": 7.02,
      "text": "GMP 여러분들을 위해 준비한 애정 듬뿍 이벤트"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.02,
      "end": 9.92,
      "text": "GMP로 영어 실력 업, 에너지도 업"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.92,
      "end": 13.43,
      "text": "더운 여름에는 시원한 아이스 커피가 딱이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.85,
      "end": 17.07,
      "text": "오늘은 아이스 아메리카노 두 잔 모바일 쿠폰 준비했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 17.73,
      "end": 19.35,
      "text": "신청 메시지 보내주신 분들 중에"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.35,
      "end": 21.29,
      "text": "다섯 분 뽑아서 보내드릴게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 22.13,
      "end": 25.07,
      "text": "담으 50원과 장문 100원에 추가 요금이 부과되는"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.07,
      "end": 27.57,
      "text": "KBS 쿨 FM 문자 샵 8910"
    },
    {
      "start": 27.57,
      "end": 31.11,
      "text": "아니면 KBS E라디오 문자 샵 1061로 신청하시거나"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.75,
      "end": 35.61,
      "text": "무료 KBS 애플리케이션 콩 또는 마이케이로 참여해주세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.61,
      "end": 65.81,
      "text": "English Morning Theater's Korean English Time"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.81,
      "end": 68.05,
      "text": "8월에는 Come On, Come On"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.05,
      "end": 72.13,
      "text": "Sweet Chemistry between Joaquin Phoenix and Woody Norman"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.13,
      "end": 74.45,
      "text": "잘 오셨습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.89,
      "end": 76.29,
      "text": "Good morning, good to be here."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.39,
      "end": 82.81,
      "text": "Yeah, wow, sweet chemistry between Joaquin Phoenix and Woody Norman이라고 외쳐주셨어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.31,
      "end": 86.35,
      "text": "확실히 it gets sweeter해지는 것 같기는 해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.35,
      "end": 93.31,
      "text": "It gets sweeter and sweeter as the uncle learns to deal with his nephew and his emotions and his own emotions."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.31,
      "end": 96.23,
      "text": "Yeah, 이렇게 시간이 점점 갈수록"
    },
    {
      "start": 96.23,
      "end": 101.71,
      "text": "Johnny 삼촌이 seems to care sincerely about his nephew."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.51,
      "end": 102.83,
      "text": "Nephew."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.47,
      "end": 104.81,
      "text": "네, 그럴 때 영어 어렵죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.13,
      "end": 105.73,
      "text": "니스는 여자."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.91,
      "end": 106.15,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.21,
      "end": 106.87,
      "text": "Nephew는 남자."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.97,
      "end": 107.89,
      "text": "헷갈리죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 108.03,
      "end": 109.13,
      "text": "Nephew도 생각해야 되고"
    },
    {
      "start": 109.13,
      "end": 110.93,
      "text": "Jesse 이름까지 생각하고 있었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.09,
      "end": 112.19,
      "text": "너무 복잡합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 112.43,
      "end": 113.33,
      "text": "Jesse, nephew."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.87,
      "end": 115.33,
      "text": "Jesse is his nephew."
    },
    {
      "start": 115.57,
      "end": 115.83,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 115.83,
      "end": 117.77,
      "text": "And he doesn't have any kids himself."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.95,
      "end": 122.11,
      "text": "So it's hard for even parents to deal with kids, especially."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.61,
      "end": 126.91,
      "text": "My brother, when my brother met my daughters, oh, he had some trouble."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.09,
      "end": 130.27,
      "text": "He lost his patience on more than one occasion."
    },
    {
      "start": 130.49,
      "end": 131.53,
      "text": "Lost his patience?"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.53,
      "end": 132.49,
      "text": "Lost his patience."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.61,
      "end": 133.83,
      "text": "뚜껑 막 열 일 번."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.95,
      "end": 134.81,
      "text": "아, 진짜요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.17,
      "end": 136.33,
      "text": "네, 한 두 번 있었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.37,
      "end": 137.55,
      "text": "어머, 어머, 어머."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.55,
      "end": 142.69,
      "text": "Yeah, my daughters treated him like their buddy, speaking Korean, very loudly to him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 143.07,
      "end": 144.23,
      "text": "and jumping on his bed."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.35,
      "end": 146.33,
      "text": "They messed up his bed completely."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.53,
      "end": 146.81,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.97,
      "end": 148.39,
      "text": "And, you know, that can be upsetting."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.63,
      "end": 148.91,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 149.03,
      "end": 150.39,
      "text": "So I said, Paul, it's okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.61,
      "end": 152.11,
      "text": "Kids are like this sometimes."
    },
    {
      "start": 152.11,
      "end": 156.99,
      "text": "이런 조카들을 둔 분들은 굉장히 와닿으실 것 같습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.43,
      "end": 162.81,
      "text": "이렇게 Jesse하고 대화하는 순간순간마다"
    },
    {
      "start": 162.81,
      "end": 165.97,
      "text": "이 삼촌인 Johnny를 보면서요,"
    },
    {
      "start": 165.97,
      "end": 170.63,
      "text": "점점 I could easily read his facial expressions."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.81,
      "end": 171.03,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.25,
      "end": 172.59,
      "text": "You could read them like a book."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.03,
      "end": 178.17,
      "text": "처음에는 되게 어색하고 뭔가 좀 거리감이 있는 그런 표정이었다면"
    },
    {
      "start": 178.17,
      "end": 180.83,
      "text": "시간이 갈수록 막 미소가 번지더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.03,
      "end": 182.09,
      "text": "Like a dad's smile."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.25,
      "end": 182.65,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.85,
      "end": 185.41,
      "text": "He starts to show his love and love him."
    },
    {
      "start": 186.13,
      "end": 187.31,
      "text": "It was really special, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 187.31,
      "end": 188.33,
      "text": "그런 intimacy."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.19,
      "end": 190.69,
      "text": "That's what the director wanted."
    },
    {
      "start": 190.77,
      "end": 192.57,
      "text": "He wanted to show that intimacy."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.91,
      "end": 195.61,
      "text": "그런 것들이 다 반영이 된 것 같습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 195.61,
      "end": 196.91,
      "text": "And he actually tried."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.07,
      "end": 197.23,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.35,
      "end": 199.29,
      "text": "He was trying to be like a dad."
    },
    {
      "start": 199.37,
      "end": 201.13,
      "text": "Because his dad is not there."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.29,
      "end": 201.57,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.71,
      "end": 202.87,
      "text": "So he was reading books."
    },
    {
      "start": 202.99,
      "end": 203.27,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.45,
      "end": 205.13,
      "text": "He was trying to read his emotions."
    },
    {
      "start": 205.65,
      "end": 208.69,
      "text": "Stuff that even actual dads don't often do."
    },
    {
      "start": 208.81,
      "end": 209.15,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.17,
      "end": 210.47,
      "text": "His uncle is doing so."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.89,
      "end": 212.07,
      "text": "근데 이제 mostly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 212.51,
      "end": 217.55,
      "text": "many kids가 like their parents to read some books before going to bed."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.55,
      "end": 218.27,
      "text": "Story books."
    },
    {
      "start": 218.53,
      "end": 220.55,
      "text": "Like fun, imaginary story books."
    },
    {
      "start": 220.65,
      "end": 221.11,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.31,
      "end": 223.79,
      "text": "분명히 우리 크쌤도 그런 경험이 있으시겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.79,
      "end": 224.61,
      "text": "Oh, 많아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.29,
      "end": 231.63,
      "text": "그러면 what kind of books have you read to your children이라고 떠오르는 책이 있나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 231.89,
      "end": 232.39,
      "text": "Dr. Seuss."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.71,
      "end": 233.89,
      "text": "Green Eggs and Ham."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.47,
      "end": 235.49,
      "text": "Sam, I Am."
    },
    {
      "start": 235.67,
      "end": 236.45,
      "text": "An English version."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.87,
      "end": 237.19,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 237.69,
      "end": 238.85,
      "text": "You have to read it."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.93,
      "end": 239.79,
      "text": "You have to read the original."
    },
    {
      "start": 240.09,
      "end": 242.09,
      "text": "So sometimes my daughters say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 242.17,
      "end": 243.09,
      "text": "You have to read this book."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.17,
      "end": 244.07,
      "text": "It's a Korean book."
    },
    {
      "start": 244.17,
      "end": 245.25,
      "text": "And then I say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 245.29,
      "end": 246.45,
      "text": "Okay, we'll read this book."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.51,
      "end": 248.39,
      "text": "And then we'll read an English book."
    },
    {
      "start": 248.39,
      "end": 250.55,
      "text": "And 항상 원래 언어."
    },
    {
      "start": 250.69,
      "end": 252.15,
      "text": "Not a 번역된 버전."
    },
    {
      "start": 252.31,
      "end": 253.37,
      "text": "No translations."
    },
    {
      "start": 254.27,
      "end": 256.95,
      "text": "So Dr. Seuss is very fun to learn English."
    },
    {
      "start": 257.07,
      "end": 258.21,
      "text": "Because it rhymes."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.47,
      "end": 259.37,
      "text": "And there's pictures."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.67,
      "end": 260.95,
      "text": "And the story is fun."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.49,
      "end": 265.89,
      "text": "So he has written many timeless classics that are great for kids."
    },
    {
      "start": 265.89,
      "end": 270.17,
      "text": "그렇게 좋은 책을 읽어주면 아이가 잠을 과연 잘 수 있을까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.97,
      "end": 272.71,
      "text": "잘 자요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.71,
      "end": 275.93,
      "text": "아니면 이 책을 읽어주면 반드시 애들이 금방 잔다."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.97,
      "end": 277.19,
      "text": "이런 꿀팁이 있으시면."
    },
    {
      "start": 277.31,
      "end": 279.21,
      "text": "그거 뭐 Dr. Seuss 그런 보장은 없고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.69,
      "end": 282.01,
      "text": "그거 뭐 롤라바이, 자전거."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.23,
      "end": 284.09,
      "text": "아하, 노래를 불러주시는 거죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.23,
      "end": 285.25,
      "text": "Rockabye, baby."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.81,
      "end": 286.53,
      "text": "그만해, 아빠."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.79,
      "end": 287.43,
      "text": "이제 잘게."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.03,
      "end": 288.75,
      "text": "그럼 바로 자요."
    },
    {
      "start": 289.13,
      "end": 289.81,
      "text": "그렇군요."
    },
    {
      "start": 289.95,
      "end": 291.33,
      "text": "아주 꿀팁이 되겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 291.45,
      "end": 292.51,
      "text": "Dr. Seuss 추천합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.51,
      "end": 293.49,
      "text": "네, 감사합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.21,
      "end": 295.95,
      "text": "자, 오늘 준비된 장면 듣고 올게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.55,
      "end": 299.87,
      "text": "I know that look in those little eyes, it's the worst."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.49,
      "end": 301.89,
      "text": "But it's okay, also."
    },
    {
      "start": 302.19,
      "end": 305.39,
      "text": "You know, you just have to explain to him that you were scared."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.55,
      "end": 307.27,
      "text": "And that's why you yelled, and then you apologized."
    },
    {
      "start": 307.63,
      "end": 309.23,
      "text": "You know, he's a person."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.35,
      "end": 310.57,
      "text": "You just be honest with him."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.31,
      "end": 312.31,
      "text": "It's called doing a repair."
    },
    {
      "start": 312.81,
      "end": 314.69,
      "text": "There's scripts for it online."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.69,
      "end": 316.13,
      "text": "Okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.27,
      "end": 319.49,
      "text": "Sounds easy."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.25,
      "end": 323.13,
      "text": "Wow, that's decayed."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.31,
      "end": 329.05,
      "text": "아니, 저라면은 엄청 놀래가지고 난리난리 나섰을 것 같은데."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.39,
      "end": 330.81,
      "text": "If you were watching the kid."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.03,
      "end": 334.15,
      "text": "그리고 엄마와 지금 조니의 통화잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.41,
      "end": 334.67,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.45,
      "end": 339.37,
      "text": "그러면 조니 was 약간 missing을 하긴 했잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 339.47,
      "end": 340.77,
      "text": "At the moment이긴 하지만."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.05,
      "end": 341.99,
      "text": "The kid was missing."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.11,
      "end": 342.29,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.37,
      "end": 343.77,
      "text": "And Johnny freaked out."
    },
    {
      "start": 343.95,
      "end": 345.89,
      "text": "I'm supposed to be watching him."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.01,
      "end": 346.99,
      "text": "Where'd he go?"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.13,
      "end": 348.87,
      "text": "It's easy, really easy to freak out."
    },
    {
      "start": 348.87,
      "end": 351.87,
      "text": "If you're a parent, or you're responsible for the kid."
    },
    {
      "start": 351.87,
      "end": 352.41,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 352.53,
      "end": 355.21,
      "text": "When you're watching this scene, I was scared to death."
    },
    {
      "start": 355.33,
      "end": 355.83,
      "text": "Me too."
    },
    {
      "start": 355.95,
      "end": 357.61,
      "text": "I'm like, whoa, was he kidnapped?"
    },
    {
      "start": 357.83,
      "end": 358.61,
      "text": "What happened?"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.69,
      "end": 359.47,
      "text": "They're in a big city."
    },
    {
      "start": 359.67,
      "end": 363.43,
      "text": "그런데 엄마의 대답은 굉장히 담담하게 이어지고 있습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.01,
      "end": 365.07,
      "text": "Mothers are wiser."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.29,
      "end": 365.55,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.81,
      "end": 366.53,
      "text": "Wiser than us."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.09,
      "end": 370.19,
      "text": "그러면 주요 표현들 하나하나 살펴보시죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 370.19,
      "end": 373.1,
      "text": "You just have to explain to him."
    },
    {
      "start": 373.26,
      "end": 375.44,
      "text": "You just have to explain to him."
    },
    {
      "start": 376.02,
      "end": 378.52,
      "text": "애한테 설명만 하면 돼."
    },
    {
      "start": 379.54,
      "end": 380.98,
      "text": "That's why you yelled."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.46,
      "end": 383.34,
